{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35a62ddd-99d6-4811-a81d-8e4629a3fc61","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n## 1. Deep Import Chain (level1 → level2 → level3)\n\nThe project imports `level1.props`, which imports `level2.props`, which imports `level3.props`. Each nested import requires MSBuild to locate, open, parse, and evaluate the file **during the evaluation phase**. Deep chains multiply this overhead and make the evaluation graph harder to parallelize.\n\n## 2. Overly Broad Glob Pattern\n\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n\nThe `**\\*.*` glob recursively scans the entire directory tree. It only excludes `bin` and `obj`, so it will traverse directories like `.git`, `node_modules`, `.vs`, `packages`, etc. MSBuild must stat every file and directory to expand this glob during evaluation. Use more specific paths or add exclusions via `DefaultItemExcludes`:\n\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.cs\" />\n```\n\nOr expand the exclusion list to cover known heavy directories.\n\n## 3. File I/O via Property Function During Evaluation\n\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n\nProperty functions execute during the **evaluation phase**, not the execution phase. Performing disk I/O here blocks evaluation—every time the project is evaluated (IDE load, design-time builds, restore), this file is read synchronously. Move file reads to a Target (execution phase) so they only run when actually building:\n\n```xml\n<Target Name=\"ReadBuildNotes\" BeforeTargets=\"Build\">\n  <ReadLinesFromFile File=\"build-notes.txt\">\n    <Output TaskParameter=\"Lines\" ItemName=\"_BuildNoteLines\" />\n  </ReadLinesFromFile>\n</Target>\n```\n\n## Evaluation vs. Execution Phase\n\nMSBuild processes a project in two stages:\n- **Evaluation** – parses XML, resolves imports, expands properties/items/globs. This runs frequently (IDE, restore, every build invocation). It must be fast.\n- **Execution** – runs Targets and Tasks. This only happens during an actual build.\n\nAll three issues above add work to the evaluation phase, slowing every interaction with the project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"071800ce-56d9-4e9f-9ff5-17c4d80d2b74","outputTokens":554,"requestId":"DBD0:2F39F8:AC71F8B:BB50D48:69FD39CE"},"id":"e069766c-6e19-4e50-baec-db3aae480784","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:18:20.488Z","parentId":"e23c7871-456a-4069-913e-70cab308c719"}
